threads.title: 820-3115B fan spins but won't turn on
threads.message:
hello

the device turns on and the backlight is not on. There was some corrosion in the q2620 area. I renewed the solders, but now the fan is spinning, there is no opening sound. I tried removing the ram and still no sound. It stays at 0.87 amps

PPBUS_G3H : 16.72 volt
PVIN_S5_HS_OTHER_ISNS : 12.8 volt
PP3V42_G3H_REG : 3,4 volt
PPVRTC_G3_OUT : 3.3 volt
PP5V_S5_LDO : 5 volt volt
PP5V_SUS_FET : 5 volt
PP3V3_S5_REG : 3.3 volt

threads.title: 820-3115B fan spins but won't turn on
threads.message:
VCORE must drop from 1.1V to 0.7V aprox when the board boots.
If stuck on 1.1V, may be RAM problem, BIOS, or PCH/CPU.

Check all SPI Bus Series Termination resistors and their traces.
Do you have DDR3 test card?
